      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS OCIO / ACEScg EXR QUICKSTART\n\nFloat VFX color-managed handoff. Requires:\n1) ComfyUI-OCIO (github.com/SlavaSexton/ComfyUI-OCIO) + `pip install opencolorio`.\n2) OpenCV with the EXR codec: opencv-python 4.x (5.x dropped it) AND set OPENCV_IO_ENABLE_OPENEXR=1 in your run .bat BEFORE python starts.\n3) [usd] extra for AtlasExportUSD (pip install atlas-camera[usd]).\n\nFlow: OCIORead loads the ACEScg .exr (input ACEScg -> output sRGB-Display as a working proxy) -> AtlasRegisterPlate records the FLOAT .exr path + ACEScg colorspace -> AtlasInput solves/meshes on the proxy -> AtlasAttachSourcePlate attaches the plate to the solve -> the Nuke/Maya/USD exporters Read the ORIGINAL .exr with colorspace='ACEScg' (not the 8-bit preview). Set OCIORead 'source' + AtlasRegisterPlate 'plate_path' to your .exr.\n\nAtlasExportNuke = SINGLE-projection scene (works at layers=0). AtlasExportNukeLayers/MayaLayers = per-band layers (need layers>=1; this example ships layers=2)."
      ]
    },
